eat, a narrative designed to delegitimize Democratic criticism of Trump ahead of a major presidential address.", "type": "attack"}, {"quote": "Tonight the President needs to talk about the issues that actually matter to the American people \u2014 the economy, the border, and getting government out of our lives.", "speaker": "Glenn Beck", "context": "Beck sets the frame for evaluating the State of the Union around conservative priorities, signaling what his audience of Torch subscribers and listeners consider the litmus test for Trump''s success.", "type": "notable_position"}], "political_attacks": ["The Left''s increasingly ''fiery rhetoric'' is characterized as dangerous and potentially inciting violence", "Democrats and progressives are framed as out of touch with the issues that ''actually matter'' to Americans", "Implicit critique that left-wing focus areas are distractions from bread-and-butter concerns like the economy and border security"], "narrative_themes": ["Left-wing rhetoric as a threat to public safety and civil discourse", "Trump as responsive to the real concerns of ordinary Americans", "Corporate greed and declining quality as a populist grievance (Hershey/Reese''s)", "Government overreach vs. individual liberty", "Border security and economic issues as top voter priorities"], "threat_level": "medium", "threat_rationale": "Beck''s framing of progressive rhetoric as physically dangerous ahead of a State of the Union address is a coordinated narrative effort to preemptively delegitimize Democratic responses and opposition, potentially suppressing the impact of progressive counter-messaging during a high-visibility political moment."}','2026-02-25T06:20:39.671932+00:00',1);
