": "claim"}, {"quote": "The Democrats don''t want you to hear these mothers'' stories because it destroys their entire narrative on immigration.", "speaker": "Steve Bannon", "context": "Directly attacks Democrats by accusing them of suppressing victims'' voices to protect a pro-immigration political agenda.", "type": "attack"}], "political_attacks": ["Democrats are accused of deliberately ignoring and silencing Angel Moms to protect their open-borders narrative", "The ''permanent political class'' and establishment figures in both parties are blamed for decades of failed immigration enforcement", "Progressives are framed as prioritizing undocumented immigrants over American citizens and crime victims"], "narrative_themes": ["Immigration as an existential threat to American safety and sovereignty", "Emotionally driven victim-centered framing to justify mass enforcement and deportation", "The State of the Union as a defining moment for the populist-nationalist movement", "Elite complicity in border failure \u2014 both parties blamed but Democrats singled out", "Populist ''us vs. them'' framing: forgotten Americans vs. the political class"], "threat_level": "high", "threat_rationale": "The episode deploys emotionally potent Angel Mom narratives timed to a major presidential address, reinforcing public support for aggressive immigration crackdowns and directly undermining progressive arguments for humane immigration reform at a moment of peak national attention."}','2026-02-25T06:20:47.818482+00:00',1);
